---
// src/pages/projects/copybot.astro
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="CopyBot - Solana Wallet & PNL Tracker" backgroundColor="#1d1c19">
  <main class="project-detail-container">
    <article class="project-detail" transition:name="copybot">
      <a href="/projects" class="back-link">
        <span class="arrow">←</span>
        <span>back to projects</span>
      </a>

      <div class="project-header">
        <h1>CopyBot</h1>
        <span class="tag">Python · Blockchain · Data</span>
      </div>

      <p class="project-intro">
        A Python-based system for monitoring, analyzing, and optimizing Solana
        copy-trading wallets using real-time on-chain data and post-trade
        performance tracking.
      </p>

      <div class="project-content">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          CopyBot is a multi-service Solana analytics tool designed to evaluate
          the effectiveness of copy-trading strategies. It ingests real-time
          wallet activity via webhooks, enriches trades with market and risk
          data, and tracks post-purchase token performance using delayed OHLCV
          analysis.
        </p>
        <p>
          Based on historical performance, the system periodically identifies
          underperforming or inactive wallets and replaces them with
          higher-performing candidates sourced from on-chain analytics
          platforms. The project emphasizes automation, asynchronous execution,
          and data-driven decision-making. The current version is under active
          rewrite, with core logic being refactored for robustness and
          scalability.
        </p>

        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Real-time Solana wallet monitoring via Helius webhooks</li>
          <li>
            Trade parsing and enrichment with pricing, metadata, and risk scores
          </li>
          <li>Delayed OHLCV-based PNL tracking for first-holder entries</li>
          <li>Automated wallet performance evaluation and replacement logic</li>
          <li>Discord-based alerts and reporting pipeline</li>
          <li>Modular, scheduled async bot architecture</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Challenges & Solutions</h2>
        <p>
          The main challenge was coordinating multiple data sources with
          different latency and rate limits while maintaining consistent state
          across services. This was addressed by decoupling ingestion, analysis,
          and optimization into independent bots orchestrated through an
          asynchronous scheduler and lightweight local data stores.
        </p>

        <div class="project-links">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/snezzz0/solana-wallet-tracker-old/"
            class="project-link-btn"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            <span>View Code</span>
            <span class="arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .project-detail-container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .back-link {
    position: absolute;
    top: -3rem;
    left: 0;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    color: #c5c9c5;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-family: "Fira Code", monospace;
    transition: color 0.2s;
    z-index: 10;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: #8ba4b0;
  }

  .arrow {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-detail {
    background: #1d1c19;
    border: 3px solid #c5c9c5;
    padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    width: 100%;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .project-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .project-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #c5c9c5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tag {
    background: #c5c9c5;
    color: #0f0f14;
    padding: 0.4rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid #c5c9c5;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .project-intro {
    color: #8ba4b0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .project-content h2 {
    color: #c5c9c5;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .project-content p {
    color: #8ba4b0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-content ul {
    color: #727169;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .project-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .project-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .project-link-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    color: #8ba4b0;
    border: 2px solid #8ba4b0;
    padding: 1rem 1.75rem;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    font-family: "Fira Code", monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .project-link-btn:hover {
    background: #8ba4b0;
    color: #0f0f14;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .project-detail-container {
      padding: 3rem 1rem 2rem;
    }

    .back-link {
      top: -2.5rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .project-detail {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .project-header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .project-header h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .project-links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .project-link-btn {
      width: 100%;
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>
